chunk_content: 72 The first priority of data collection and reporting of PrEP among key populations must be to do no harm. These data must be managed confidentially to ensure the identities of individuals are protected and to prevent further stigma and discrimination of key populations. P R E NOTE: In accordance to PrEP guidance, not all PrEP beneficiaries are expected to fall within the KP V disaggregates; therefore, the total disaggregations for KP does not have to sum to the numerator E total. Both KP-specific and clinical partners should complete these KP disaggregations, but only if safe N to maintain these files and to report.
